    question: "Does anxiety in children usually need medication?",
    answer: "Not usually at first — for mild-to-moderate anxiety in 8–10-year-olds, cognitive behavioral therapy, or CBT, is considered first-line treatment and helps many children improve significantly (AACAP, 2020). Medication may be considered for more severe symptoms, but that decision should be made with your pediatrician and a qualified mental health clinician."
